<%# "Signing you in…" interstitial for GET /magic_link/:token.

    SCANNER-SAFE BY DESIGN, no manual tap: the GET still does NOT consume the
    token — it renders a form that AUTO-SUBMITS via JS on load. A real browser
    POSTs instantly and signs the human in (no second click); email link-scanners
    / the Gmail image proxy / SafeLinks / corporate AV issue a no-JS GET, never
    run the script, and so can't burn the single-use token before the human
    arrives. The visible button is the no-JS fallback.

    button_to emits a real <form> with the CSRF authenticity token; the consume
    POST is same-origin and the confirm response sets Referrer-Policy:
    strict-origin (see MagicLinksController#confirm) so the Origin header stays
    intact and the POST passes origin-based CSRF. %>
<div class="min-h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center">
  <div class="w-full max-w-md">
    <div class="text-center mb-8">
      <img src="/icon-192.png" alt="Turf Totals" width="80" height="80" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full shadow-lg mx-auto mb-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-heading tracking-tight">Turf <span class="text-primary">Totals</span></h1>
      <p class="text-secondary mt-2">Signing you in&hellip;</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card shadow p-8 text-center">
      <%# Spinner shown while the auto-submit fires (the page redirects in <1s). %>
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-6" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg class="animate-spin w-8 h-8 text-primary" style="animation: spin 1s linear infinite;"
             xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <circle class="opacity-25" cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"></circle>
          <path class="opacity-75" fill="currentColor" d="M4 12a8 8 0 018-8V0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12h4z"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <%# No-JS fallback: a real CSRF-protected POST button. JS auto-submits this
          same form on load so JS browsers never need to click it. %>
      <%= button_to magic_link_consume_path(token: @token),
            method: :post,
            form: { id: "magic-consume-form", data: { turbo: "false" } },
            class: "btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full" do %>
        Sign in to Turf Totals
      <% end %>

      <p class="text-xs text-muted text-center mt-4">
        Almost there&hellip; if you're not redirected automatically, tap the button above.
        This link expires shortly and can only be used once.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%# Inline keyframe so the spinner animates even if the `animate-spin` utility
    isn't in the compiled CSS bundle. %>
<style>@keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }</style>

<script>
  (function () {
    var form = document.getElementById('magic-consume-form');
    if (!form || form.dataset.autoSubmitted) return;
    // Auto-submit so the human signs in on link-click with no extra tap. A no-JS
    // scanner GET never reaches this, so the single-use token stays safe.
    form.dataset.autoSubmitted = '1';
    if (typeof form.requestSubmit === 'function') form.requestSubmit();
    else form.submit();
  })();
</script>
